cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the design and analysis of a wireless surveillance system, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT), as well as security and cryptography (cs.CR). The system also involves wireless networking (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY) for the optimization of the jamming power and beamforming vectors. Finally, the use of multiple antennas for improved performance falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
